you might read to us?

25
00:01:17,828 --> 00:01:19,159
[woman] Oh, I'd love to.

26
00:01:20,205 --> 00:01:24,164
Whoever has no house now
Will never have one.

27
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:27,710
Whoever is alone will stay alone

28
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:32,415
Will sit, read, write long letters
Through the evening

29
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:36,093
And wander the boulevards
Up and down, restlessly

30
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:38,511
While the dry leaves are blowing.

31
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:40,215
[man] Goodness, that harsh, isn't it?

32
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:44,177
