[Caden] Sammy!

1439
01:39:45,062 --> 01:39:46,894
I didn't jump, Sammy!

1440
01:39:48,441 --> 01:39:51,024
A man stopped me before I jumped. Get up!

1441
01:39:53,446 --> 01:39:54,527
I didn't jump.

1442
01:39:56,073 --> 01:39:58,064
[whispering indistinctly]

1443
01:40:01,787 --> 01:40:03,528
I know how to do it now.

1444
01:40:04,499 --> 01:40:07,161
There are nearly 13 million people
in the world.

1445
01:40:07,960 --> 01:40:09,917
I mean, can you imagine that many people?

1446
01:40:10,004 --> 01:40:12,211
And none of those people is an extra.

1447
01:40:14,050 --> 01:40:18,965
They're all leads in their own stories.
They have to be given their due.

1448
01:40:20,723 --> 01:40:22,259
[actor] I know how to do it now.

1449
01:40:22,350 --> 01:40:24,432
There are 13 million people in this world.

1450
01:40:24,519 --> 01:40:26,681
Can you imagine how many people that is?

1451
01:40:27,563 --> 01:40:31,682
None of those people are an extra.
They're all a lead in their own story.

1452
01:40:31,776 --> 01:40:33,983
They have got to be given their due.

1453
01:40:34,070 --> 01:40:35,526
Do you see what I'm saying?

1454
01:40:37,198 --> 01:40:38,279
[Hazel] Come over tonight.

1455
01:40:42,245 --> 01:40:43,235
Please.

1456
01:40:45,706 --> 01:40:47,743
[Caden] You know,
we could get a place together.

1457
01:40:47,833 --> 01:40:52,452
- We could get a loft.
- God, Caden, that sounds nice.

1458
01:40:52,547 --> 01:40:55,289
I miss my daughter.
Maybe she could come live with us.

1459
01:40:55,383 --> 01:40:56,589
I miss Olive.

1460
01:40:58,177 --> 01:40:59,667
And the other one.

1461
01:41:00,388 --> 01:41:02,925
- I'm a bad person.
- Oh, no, you're not.

1462
01:41:03,015 --> 01:41:05,882
I am. I should never have
gone out with Sammy.

1463
01:41:07,019 --> 01:41:09,511
I was just trying to get to you.

1464
01:41:09,605 --> 01:41:12,188
You can't cause someone to kill himself.

1465
01:41:13,234 --> 01:41:14,565
He was very troubled.

1466
01:41:15,736 --> 01:41:17,022
God, Caden.

1467
01:41:20,616 --> 01:41:22,698
I wish we had this when we were young.

1468
01:41:26,622 --> 01:41:28,659
And all those years in between.

1469
01:41:28,749 --> 01:41:30,581
My heart aches so much for you.

1470
01:41:31,419 --> 01:41:33,126
We're here, Caden.

1471
01:41:34,964 --> 01:41:38,707
- I'm here.
- I'm aching for it being over.

1472
01:41:41,304 --> 01:41:44,763
Yeah. The end is built into the beginning.

1473
01:41:46,350 --> 01:41:47,806
What can you do?

1474
01:41:48,769 --> 01:41:51,761
- God, you're just perfect.
- I'm a mess.

1475
01:41:53,274 --> 01:41:55,982
- But we fit, don't we?
- Yeah.

1476
01:42:07,413 --> 01:42:09,370
[Caden] It doesn't always
happen for me now

1477
01:42:09,457 --> 01:42:12,165
because of the medication and everything.

1478
01:42:12,251 --> 01:42:15,209
- I take a lot of pills.
- It's okay.

1479
01:42:16,505 --> 01:42:21,841
Uh, I'm embarrassed. I don't want you
to think it's about you or me.

1480
01:42:21,927 --> 01:42:22,962
It's okay.

1481
01:42:25,514 --> 01:42:27,505
[tender music playing]

1482
01:43:08,474 --> 01:43:09,635
I have a title.

1483
01:43:12,395 --> 01:43:16,889
The Obscure Moon
Lighting an Obscure World.

1484
01:43:21,570 --> 01:43:23,607
I think it might be too much.

1485
01:43:26,158 --> 01:43:27,614
Yeah, probably.

1486
01:43:29,620 --> 01:43:30,610
[Caden chuckles]

1487
01:43:40,715 --> 01:43:42,376
[man] Sir, could you come up here, please?

1488
01:44:01,402 --> 01:44:03,109
Might be smoke inhalation.

1489
01:44:09,034 --> 01:44:11,822
[Hazel on recording] It's Hazel.
Leave a message or not. It's your dime.

1490
01:44:11,912 --> 01:44:14,370
- [beeps]
- I know how to do the play now.

1491
01:44:18,294 --> 01:44:21,002
It'll all take place
over the course of one day,

1492
01:44:23,132 --> 01:44:25,419
and that day will be the day
before you died.

1493
01:44:27,887 --> 01:44:29,878
It was the happiest day of my life.

1494
01:44:33,642 --> 01:44:35,553
And I'll be able to relive it forever.

1495
01:44:36,854 --> 01:44:37,969
See you soon.

1496
01:44:43,819 --> 01:44:48,063
So have you got any thoughts
for, uh, today's rehearsal?

1497
01:44:50,201 --> 01:44:52,784
- l have a new title, maybe.
- Oh.

1498
01:44:52,870 --> 01:44:54,611
Infectious Diseases in Cattle.

1499
01:44:55,498 --> 01:44:56,488
Oh.

1500
01:44:59,460 --> 01:45:02,623
The title means a lot of things.
You'll see, it means a lot.

1501
01:45:04,298 --> 01:45:06,414
[clock ticking]

1502
01:45:14,892 --> 01:45:16,849
I need a Caden for my Hazel.

1503
01:45:18,687 --> 01:45:20,678
I'd very much like to play Caden.

1504
01:45:22,358 --> 01:45:25,601
[, uh-- I know that--

1505
01:45:25,694 --> 01:45:28,857
I know
that it would be nontraditional casting,

1506
01:45:29,657 --> 01:45:33,400
but I think I could do it.
I think I understand him.

1507
01:45:33,494 --> 01:45:35,235
I don't understand him.

1508
01:45:35,329 --> 01:45:40,870
Well, Caden Cotard is a man already dead.

1509
01:45:42,002 --> 01:45:48,749
He, um... He lives in a half world
between stasis and antistasis,

1510
01:45:48,843 --> 01:45:52,802
and time is concentrated,
chronology confused.

1511
01:45:52,888 --> 01:45:58,554
Yet up until recently,
he's strived valiantly...

1512
01:46:00,145 --> 01:46:03,604
to make sense of his situation.
But now, he, uh...

1513
01:46:04,483 --> 01:46:05,894
He's turned to stone.

1514
01:46:07,945 --> 01:46:11,609
- Okay. Sounds good.
- Okay.

1515
01:46:13,075 --> 01:46:15,442
- Thanks.
- She's right? [stammers]

1516
01:46:15,536 --> 01:46:18,528
I didn't see that at all.
I saw it as much more hopeful.

1517
01:46:20,875 --> 01:46:23,617
None of those people is extras.

1518
01:46:24,420 --> 01:46:26,832
They're all leads in their own stories.

1519
01:46:30,926 --> 01:46:34,510
No, this is tedious. This is nothing.

1520
01:46:38,767 --> 01:46:41,384
[whispering] Hi, your scene's over.
Would you leave the stage?

1521
01:46:41,478 --> 01:46:44,436
- What is she doing?
- He's directing.

1522
01:46:44,523 --> 01:46:46,855
Can I get you down at the coffin there?

1523
01:46:47,693 --> 01:46:50,276
[Michael] She not getting
the feel of you, Caden.

1524
01:46:50,362 --> 01:46:52,820
You don't move around like that.
You don't talk to people.

1525
01:46:57,828 --> 01:46:59,034
Sit on the ground there.

1526
01:46:59,121 --> 01:47:00,657
Okay, everybody, let's run it.

1527
01:47:03,417 --> 01:47:05,704
Everything is more complicated
than you think.

1528
01:47:06,420 --> 01:47:09,412
You only see a tenth of what is true.

1529
01:47:09,506 --> 01:47:14,171
There are a million little strings
attached to every choice you make.

1530
01:47:14,887 --> 01:47:17,470
You can destroy your life
every time you choose.

1531
01:47:17,556 --> 01:47:20,298
But maybe you won't know for 20 years,

1532
01:47:21,352 --> 01:47:23,889
and you may never, ever trace it
to its source.

1533
01:47:23,979 --> 01:47:26,562
And you only get one chance
to play it out.

1534
01:47:26,649 --> 01:47:29,516
Just try and figure out your own divorce.

1535
01:47:30,361 --> 01:47:34,525
And they say there is no fate,
but there is, it's what you create.

1536
01:47:36,325 --> 01:47:39,067
And even though the world goes on
for eons and eons,

1537
01:47:39,161 --> 01:47:43,621
you are only here for a fraction
of a fraction of a second.

1538
01:47:43,707 --> 01:47:46,995
Most of your time is spent being dead
or not yet born.

1539
01:47:47,086 --> 01:47:50,624
But while alive, you wait in vain,

1540
01:47:50,714 --> 01:47:54,753
wasting years for a phone call
or a letter or a look

1541
01:47:54,843 --> 01:47:57,210
from someone or something
to make it all right.

1542
01:47:57,304 --> 01:48:01,138
And it never comes, or it seems to,
but it doesn't really.

1543
01:48:02,601 --> 01:48:04,842
So you spend your time in vague regret

1544
01:48:04,937 --> 01:48:08,680
or vaguer hope that something good
will come along.

1545
01:48:08,774 --> 01:48:10,560
Something to make you feel connected.

1546
01:48:10,651 --> 01:48:13,063
Something to make you feel whole.

1547
01:48:13,153 --> 01:48:15,485
Something to make you feel loved.

1548
01:48:15,572 --> 01:48:17,313
[gospel music playing over speakers]

1549
01:48:17,408 --> 01:48:18,569
And the truth is...

1550
01:48:20,452 --> 01:48:21,942
I feel so angry.

1551
01:48:23,998 --> 01:48:25,238
And the truth is...

1552
01:48:26,583 --> 01:48:29,075
I feel so fucking sad.

1553
01:48:31,046 --> 01:48:36,837
And the truth is, I've felt
so fucking hurt for so fucking long.

1554
01:48:36,927 --> 01:48:39,840
And for just as long,
I've been pretending I'm okay

1555
01:48:39,930 --> 01:48:42,513
just to get along, just for...

1556
01:48:42,599 --> 01:48:44,431
[mourners sobbing]

1557
01:48:44,518 --> 01:48:45,633
I don't know why.

1558
01:48:46,311 --> 01:48:50,225
Maybe because no one wants
to hear about my misery...

1559
01:48:51,859 --> 01:48:53,349
because they have their own.

1560
01:48:57,531 --> 01:48:59,272
Well, fuck everybody.

1561
01:49:01,910 --> 01:49:03,821
- Amen.
- Amen.

1562
01:49:20,471 --> 01:49:22,633
- Delightful.
- Thanks.

1563
01:49:22,723 --> 01:49:24,384
I'm out of ideas.

1564
01:49:27,644 --> 01:49:28,805
I'm dead.

1565
01:49:31,106 --> 01:49:36,101
Well, I could take over as you for a bit
until you feel refreshed.

1566
01:49:36,820 --> 01:49:39,903
I think you're tired, Caden.
All these years of creative work.

1567
01:49:41,450 --> 01:49:46,695
I think you just need some time
to regroup.

1568
01:49:48,540 --> 01:49:52,033
- I need to keep my hand in.
- Well, Ellen needs to be filled.

1569
01:49:52,127 --> 01:49:55,210
- What do you mean?
- Her role. Just for a bit.

1570
01:49:55,297 --> 01:49:56,628
It's a choice role.

1571
01:49:59,510 --> 01:50:00,966
I do like to clean.

1572
01:50:16,360 --> 01:50:17,191
Ellen?

1573
01:50:22,616 --> 01:50:26,530
- Yes?
- Caden asked me to give you this.

1574
01:50:26,620 --> 01:50:29,829
You're to keep it in all the time.

1575
01:50:34,461 --> 01:50:37,920
[Millicent on radio] So touched
by the sadness of Adele's neighbor

1576
01:50:38,006 --> 01:50:39,212
so close to death.

1577
01:50:41,093 --> 01:50:43,209
Say, "Thank you," to Adele's neighbor.

1578
01:50:43,762 --> 01:50:45,002
Thank you.

1579
01:50:45,097 --> 01:50:47,680
You're very welcome, young lady.

1580
01:50:47,766 --> 01:50:51,225
- Now say, "Have a very good day."
- Have a very good day.

1581
01:50:51,311 --> 01:50:52,767
I will indeed.

1582
01:50:57,734 --> 01:50:59,316
Reach for the toilet paper.

1583
01:51:01,029 --> 01:51:02,815
Wrap some around your hand.

1584
01:51:04,199 --> 01:51:05,405
Wipe yourself.

1585
01:51:08,954 --> 01:51:10,945
[monitor beeping]

1586
01:51:11,415 --> 01:51:13,622
There was supposed to be something else.

1587
01:51:15,210 --> 01:51:18,874
You were supposed
to have something, a calm.

1588
01:51:19,882 --> 01:51:20,872
Love.

1589
01:51:21,925 --> 01:51:22,915
Children.

1590
01:51:23,969 --> 01:51:25,801
A child, at least.

1591
01:51:27,472 --> 01:51:28,553
Children.

1592
01:51:30,517 --> 01:51:31,507
Meaning.

1593
01:51:39,276 --> 01:51:41,142
Everything okay, Eric?

1594
01:51:44,156 --> 01:51:47,694
- Everything is everything.
- [Ellen] He hates me.

1595
01:51:49,870 --> 01:51:52,328
I disappointed him, and he hates me.

1596
01:51:54,833 --> 01:51:57,871
Everyone is disappointing
when you know someone.

1597
01:52:03,800 --> 01:52:08,089
[Ellen] I remember having that picnic
with my mother. Look at me.

1598
01:52:08,972 --> 01:52:10,007
Ellen, what is it?

1599
01:52:11,141 --> 01:52:12,347
I was so young.

1600
01:52:13,435 --> 01:52:16,473
I'm going to remember this moment
for the rest of my life, Mama,

1601
01:52:16,563 --> 01:52:20,431
and in exactly 20 years,
come here with my daughter

1602
01:52:21,193 --> 01:52:22,979
and have exactly the same picnic.

1603
01:52:23,070 --> 01:52:24,060
There was so much hope.

1604
01:52:24,154 --> 01:52:26,566
Baby, that's the loveliest thing
I've ever heard.

1605
01:52:29,826 --> 01:52:34,286
Oh, God. Sorry, Mommy. I'm sorry.

1606
01:52:54,685 --> 01:52:56,426
Where is my little girl?

1607
01:52:57,145 --> 01:53:01,389
Where is my little girl?
Where is my little girl?

1608
01:53:11,952 --> 01:53:14,410
Look at the night table
for a note from Adele.

1609
01:53:16,373 --> 01:53:18,364
[computer reading on-screen text]

1610
01:53:23,130 --> 01:53:24,495
Stare out the window.

1611
01:53:27,092 --> 01:53:30,881
Remember the time she got you
to pose for one of her paintings?

1612
01:53:30,971 --> 01:53:33,633
How she told you how beautiful you were?

1613
01:53:33,724 --> 01:53:36,842
How she made you feel pretty again
for a little while?

1614
01:53:37,853 --> 01:53:39,309
Think how you'll miss her.

1615
01:53:40,897 --> 01:53:41,887
Stand up.

1616
01:53:49,239 --> 01:53:50,946
[explosions in distance]

1617
01:53:51,033 --> 01:53:54,196
Now it is waiting, and nobody cares.

1618
01:53:55,037 --> 01:53:58,200
And when your wait is over,
this room will still exist...

1619
01:53:58,290 --> 01:53:59,325
[crowd clamoring]

1620
01:53:59,416 --> 01:54:04,001
...and it will continue to hold shoes
and dresses and boxes

1621
01:54:04,087 --> 01:54:07,955
and maybe someday
another waiting person. And maybe not.

1622
01:54:08,050 --> 01:54:09,666
- [woman] What do we want?
- [crowd] Freedom!

1623
01:54:09,760 --> 01:54:11,296
The room doesn't care either.

1624
01:54:13,430 --> 01:54:15,421
[clamoring continues]

1625
01:54:25,192 --> 01:54:27,183
[explosion]

1626
01:54:28,612 --> 01:54:30,319
- [Millicent] Hello?
- [static buzzes on radio]

1627
01:54:31,656 --> 01:54:33,238
[door opens]

1628
01:54:34,659 --> 01:54:37,117
[groans, then sighs]

1629
01:54:50,717 --> 01:54:53,835
There's nobody running
the elevator anymore.

1630
01:55:03,855 --> 01:55:05,061
[man screams]

1631
01:55:06,650 --> 01:55:08,641
[dramatic music playing]

1632
01:55:29,756 --> 01:55:33,750
[Millicent] What was once before you,
an exciting and mysterious future,

1633
01:55:33,844 --> 01:55:38,634
is now behind you,
lived, understood, disappointing.

1634
01:55:39,599 --> 01:55:41,385
You realize you are not special.

1635
01:55:42,227 --> 01:55:47,017
You have struggled into existence
and are now slipping silently out of it.

1636
01:55:47,649 --> 01:55:51,267
This is everyone's experience.
Every single one.

1637
01:55:51,903 --> 01:55:56,022
The specifics hardly matter.
Everyone is everyone.

1638
01:55:56,950 --> 01:55:58,281
So you are Adele,

1639
01:55:59,035 --> 01:56:02,744
Hazel, Claire, Olive.

1640
01:56:04,749 --> 01:56:09,494
You are Ellen.
All her meager sadnesses are yours.

1641
01:56:09,588 --> 01:56:13,422
All her loneliness.
The gray, straw-like hair.

1642
01:56:14,092 --> 01:56:18,131
Her red, raw hands. It's yours.

1643
01:56:18,221 --> 01:56:20,679
It is time for you to understand this.

1644
01:56:32,194 --> 01:56:33,184
Walk.

1645
01:56:40,494 --> 01:56:43,612
As the people who adore you
stop adoring you,

1646
01:56:43,705 --> 01:56:45,992
as they die, as they move on,

1647
01:56:46,875 --> 01:56:50,834
as you shed them, as you shed
your beauty, your youth,

1648
01:56:51,546 --> 01:56:55,540
as the world forgets you,
as you recognize your transience,

1649
01:56:55,634 --> 01:56:59,468
as you begin to lose
your characteristics one by one,

1650
01:56:59,554 --> 01:57:00,760
as you learn
there is no one watching you,

1651
01:57:00,764 --> 01:57:01,845
as you learn
there is no one watching you,

1652
01:57:01,932 --> 01:57:05,971
and there never was,
you think only about driving.

1653
01:57:06,061 --> 01:57:10,305
Not coming from anyplace,
not arriving anyplace,

1654
01:57:10,398 --> 01:57:13,481
just driving, counting off time.

1655
01:57:14,569 --> 01:57:17,186
Now you are here. It's 7:43.

1656
01:57:18,031 --> 01:57:21,069
Now you are here. It's 7:44.

1657
01:57:21,159 --> 01:57:23,867
Now you are... gone.

1658
01:57:31,461 --> 01:57:32,826
[Caden] Where is everybody?

1659
01:57:34,798 --> 01:57:36,254
Mostly dead.

1660
01:57:37,801 --> 01:57:38,962
Some have left.

1661
01:57:46,309 --> 01:57:51,975
Would you sit with me for a moment?
'Cause I'm very tired and lonely.

1662
01:58:12,711 --> 01:58:13,997
I feel like I know you.

1663
01:58:15,422 --> 01:58:19,916
Well, I was the, um,
mother in Ellen's dream.

1664
01:58:20,010 --> 01:58:21,000
Yes.

1665
01:58:24,347 --> 01:58:27,214
You seem a bit older than I remember.

1666
01:58:27,309 --> 01:58:29,050
That dream was quite a while ago.

1667
01:58:29,144 --> 01:58:30,555
[static buzzes on radio]

1668
01:58:30,645 --> 01:58:32,056
[Millicent] Apologize.

1669
01:58:32,856 --> 01:58:34,767
I didn't mean to say you looked old.

1670
01:58:34,858 --> 01:58:36,940
[somber music playing]

1671
01:58:45,368 --> 01:58:48,110
There's everyone's dreams
in all those apartments.

1672
01:58:51,541 --> 01:58:56,661
All those thoughts I'll never know.
That's the truth of it.

1673
01:59:02,218 --> 01:59:05,051
I wanted to do that picnic
with my daughter.

1674
01:59:09,643 --> 01:59:11,975
I feel like
I've disappointed you terribly.

1675
01:59:12,062 --> 01:59:16,351
Oh, no. I am so proud of you.

1676
01:59:17,442 --> 01:59:20,059
Ask her if you can put your head
on her shoulder.

1677
01:59:20,153 --> 01:59:22,360
Can I lay my head on your shoulder?

1678
01:59:23,365 --> 01:59:24,355
Yes.

1679
01:59:34,417 --> 01:59:35,578
I love you.

1680
01:59:39,673 --> 01:59:40,834
I love you too.

1681
02:00:04,030 --> 02:00:05,987
